#~ msgid ""
#~ "If you do not have a &latex; binary which includes inverse search "
#~ "information natively, you need an additional file (additional files are "
#~ "referred to as <emphasis>packages</emphasis> in &latex;) called "
#~ "<filename>srcltx.sty</filename>. You will have to do a search of your "
#~ "files to check whether your distribution has <filename>scrltx.sty</"
#~ "filename> included. If it is not included, you may <ulink url=\"http://"
#~ "valis.cs.uiuc.edu/~sariel/research/latex/srcltx.sty\">download it</"
#~ "ulink>; copy it to a &tex; folder, for example <userinput>/usr/share/"
#~ "texmf/tex/latex/srcltx/</userinput>, and run <userinput><command>texhash</"
#~ "command></userinput> so that &latex; will know its whereabouts. Then you "
#~ "can set the following command into the preamble:"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Se non hai un file binario &latex; che includa le informazioni di ricerca "
#~ "all'indietro da sé, hai bisogno di un file aggiuntivo (i file aggiuntivi "
#~ "sono indicati come <emphasis>pacchetti</emphasis> in &latex;), chiamato "
#~ "<filename>srcltx.sty</filename>. Dovrai fare una ricerca tra i tuoi file "
#~ "per controllare se la tua distribuzione include <filename>srcltx.sty</"
#~ "filename>. Se non è incluso, puoi <ulink url=\"http://valis.cs.uiuc.edu/"
#~ "~sariel/research/latex/srcltx.sty\">scaricarlo</ulink>; copialo in una "
#~ "cartella di &tex;, per esempio <userinput>/usr/share/texmf/tex/latex/"
#~ "srcltx/</userinput>, ed esegui <userinput><command>texhash</command></"
#~ "userinput> in modo che &latex; sia al corrente della sua esistenza. "
#~ "Quindi devi impostare il seguente comando nel preambolo:"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "\\documentclass[12pt, a4paper]{book}\n"
#~ "        \\usepackage[active]{srcltx}\n"
#~ "        \\pagestyle{empty}\n"
#~ "        \\renewcommand{\\baselinestretch}{2}\n"
#~ "        \\begin{document}\n"
#~ "        \\begin{verse}\n"
#~ "        The KDE \\LaTeX\\ source code editor &kile; is my favorite.\n"
#~ "                \n"
#~ "        \\emph{Because} it is easy to use!\n"
#~ "        \\end{verse}\n"
#~ "        \\end{document}"
